article.headline: Robert Morris 91, Canisius 73
article.story: CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- Jimmy Langhurst led four Robert Morris players in double figures with 21 points to lead the Colonials to a 91-73 victory over Canisius on Wednesday. Langhurst was 7 of 10 on 3-pointers for Robert Morris (7-4). Jeremy Chappell added 19 points for the Colonials, while A.J. Jackson had 15 and Tony Lee had a double-double with 14 points and a game-high 10 assists. Frank Turner and Pawel Malesa each scored 17 points for Canisius (1-9) and Jovan Robinson added 13 points. Robert Morris shot 51.5 percent from the field and 47.1 percent from 3-point range and converted 16 turnovers into 20 points. Canisius shot 47.3 percent from the field and 38.5 percent from 3-point range. Robert Morris ended the first half with a 45-34 lead. The Colonials lead the series 6-1 against the Golden Griffins.
